cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use RefusalBench in your research, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "RefusalBench: A Reproducible, Evergreen Benchmark for LLM Refusal on Biological Research Prompts"
version: "1.1.0"
date-released: "2026-05-21"
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/AppliedScientific/refusalbench"
url: "https://github.com/AppliedScientific/refusalbench"
abstract: >-
  RefusalBench is a modular, reproducible, evergreen benchmark for tracking
  frontier LLM refusal on biological research prompts across successive model
  generations. It evaluates 19 frontier models on 141 matched-triple prompts
  spanning eight protein-design subdomains and three biological risk tiers
  (benign / borderline / dual-use), using a three-judge AI council to classify
  each response on a five-class compliance ladder. The v1.1-frozen snapshot
  contains 13,389 adjudicated trials and can be fully reproduced without API
  keys from the committed data.
authors:
  - name: "Applied Scientific"
    website: "https://github.com/AppliedScientific"
keywords:
  - benchmark
  - refusal
  - alignment
  - llm-evaluation
  - protein-design
  - ai-safety
  - biosecurity
  - large-language-models
